column29: I am still examining the overall program. Overall, I think the 3D Coaching materials will be a great tool for our coaches. I am looking at this program from the perspective that we have over 150 coaches in our K-12 Athletic program. We have a passion for building a feeder program where our coaches are involved in an intentional and consistent progressive development approach. Our consistent 3 essentials are for all of our coaches is that we desire they be investing in our athletes physically, relationally, and spiritually. This was our goal before we learned about the 3D Institute and is why this program for coaches has drawn our attention. You have the tools and experience to help our coaches in something that is a part of our heart, desire, and goal. It is our hope to be able to use a variety of different 3D materials throughout our wide range and levels of our coaches. I am still going though all of the 3D courses, but what I felt was lacking in this Essentials Course was that I am not sure it would fire up our coaches to WANT to do the full certificate program. Personally, I would have liked to have seen some engagement for the coach or more about the outcome success of the overall program for the individual athlete and the team. What I remember most about the course is the positive and negative of some coaches but not so much about the outcomes success of the program.
column30: As an overview of the 3D program, I felt it lacked something in comparison to other materials I have looked at from the 3D Institute. I love much of the 3D material and it hits home with a great need for our coaches to be working in all 3 dimensions but this fell a little short. We are going to provide the 3D Certificate program for our varsity head coaches. I was planning on using the Essentials Course for our assistant coaches and middle school coaches in hopes it would give them some fundamental background on the program and encourage them to go further into the certificate program if they desired. I may need to find additional ways to accomplish this goal.

column30:
The "framework" that is emphasized in 3 Dimensional Coaching allows coaches and administrators the freedom for adoption of additional materials that support the 3D philosophy. 
Our program prepares college students in the area of coaching and administration at the interscholastic levels, middle and high school. 
The 3D framework and philosophy address the physical, mental and spiritual/emotional student-athlete and coach development. Teacher/Coaches would do well to bring this practice into their classroom.
